<li id="cite_note-8"><b><a href="#cite_ref-8" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="web"><a href="https://bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi?id=236933" class="external text" title="https://bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi?id=236933" rel="nofollow">"Bugzilla@Mozilla - Bug 236933 - Disable SSL2 and other weak ciphers"</a>. <a href="/wiki/Mozilla_Corporation" title="Mozilla Corporation">Mozilla Corporation</a><span class="printonly">. <a href="https://bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi?id=236933" class="external free" title="https://bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi?id=236933" rel="nofollow">https://bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi?id=236933</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 2007-11-25</span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=Bugzilla%40Mozilla+-+Bug+236933+-+Disable+SSL2+and+other+weak+ciphers&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft.pub=%5B%5BMozilla+Corporation%5D%5D&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbugzilla.mozilla.org%2Fshow_bug.cgi%3Fid%3D236933&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Transport_Layer_Security"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-9"><b><a href="#cite_ref-9" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="web"><a href="https://bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi?id=454759" class="external text" title="https://bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi?id=454759" rel="nofollow">"Firefox still sends SSLv2 handshake even though the protocol is disabled"</a>. <span class="mw-formatted-date" title="2008-09-11"><a href="/wiki/2008" title="2008">2008</a>-<a href="/wiki/September_11" title="September 11">09-11</a></span><span class="printonly">. <a href="https://bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi?id=454759" class="external free" title="https://bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi?id=454759" rel="nofollow">https://bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi?id=454759</a></span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=Firefox+still+sends+SSLv2+handshake+even+though+the+protocol+is+disabled&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft.date=%5B%5B2008-09-11%5D%5D&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbugzilla.mozilla.org%2Fshow_bug.cgi%3Fid%3D454759&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Transport_Layer_Security"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-10"><b><a href="#cite_ref-10" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="web" id="CITEREFPettersen">Pettersen, Yngve (<span class="mw-formatted-date" title="2007-04-30"><a href="/wiki/2007" title="2007">2007</a>-<a href="/wiki/April_30" title="April 30">04-30</a></span>). <a href="http://my.opera.com/yngve/blog/2007/04/30/10-years-of-ssl-in-opera" class="external text" title="http://my.opera.com/yngve/blog/2007/04/30/10-years-of-ssl-in-opera" rel="nofollow">"10 years of SSL in Opera - Implementer's notes"</a>. <a href="/wiki/Opera_Software" title="Opera Software">Opera Software</a><span class="printonly">. <a href="http://my.opera.com/yngve/blog/2007/04/30/10-years-of-ssl-in-opera" class="external free" title="http://my.opera.com/yngve/blog/2007/04/30/10-years-of-ssl-in-opera" rel="nofollow">http://my.opera.com/yngve/blog/2007/04/30/10-years-of-ssl-in-opera</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 2007-11-25</span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=10+years+of+SSL+in+Opera+-+Implementer%27s+notes&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft.aulast=Pettersen&amp;rft.aufirst=Yngve&amp;rft.au=Pettersen%2C+Yngve&amp;rft.date=%5B%5B2007-04-30%5D%5D&amp;rft.pub=%5B%5BOpera+Software%5D%5D&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fmy.opera.com%2Fyngve%2Fblog%2F2007%2F04%2F30%2F10-years-of-ssl-in-opera&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Transport_Layer_Security"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-11"><b><a href="#cite_ref-11" title="">^</a></b> "<a href="http://technet.microsoft.com/en-us/library/cc785811.aspx" class="external text" title="http://technet.microsoft.com/en-us/library/cc785811.aspx" rel="nofollow">SSL/TLS in Detail</a>". <i><a href="/wiki/Microsoft_TechNet" title="Microsoft TechNet">Microsoft TechNet</a></i>. Updated July 31, 2003.</li>
<li id="cite_note-openpgp-12">^ <a href="#cite_ref-openpgp_12-0" title=""><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-openpgp_12-1" title=""><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> These certificates are currently <a href="/wiki/X.509" title="X.509">X.509</a>, but there is also a draft specifying the use of <a href="/wiki/OpenPGP" title="OpenPGP" class="mw-redirect">OpenPGP</a> based certificates.</li>
